Secretory/excretory pore opens opposite nucleus of pharyngeal gland; duct obscure; secretory/excretory cell not seen. Hemizonid over ~2 annules, 5 or 6 annules anterior to pore (
Fig. 3A
).

Uterus packed with sperm in inseminated females, occupying ~60% of body length; vagina perpendicular to body axis, appears to be surrounded by strong muscles; reproductive tract hypertrophied in some specimens. Vulva a transverse slit, vulval lips flat, no vulval plate present. Anus an obscure pore. Tail short; length 1–1.5 times diameter at anus, tip distinctly notched (
Fig. 3L
).
